    (date "2026-07-14")
    (rev "A0")
    (comment 1 "Architecture level A: functional hierarchy, no part numbers")
  )
  (text "SYSTEM POWER FLOW:\nBAT1/BAT2 -> PCB-A_BFE_POWER -> PACK_BUS -> PCB-C_POWER_12V / PCB-D_POWER_5V / PCB-E_LIGHT_POWER / PCB-B_CTRL_RESERVE.\nPCB-B provides MCU, critical power, EMG, RS-485 and control/diagnostics."
    (at 20 25 0)
    (effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)) (justify left))
  )
  (text "SAFETY RULES:\n1. No central K_MAIN.\n2. K_BATx is monostable self-hold and opens on BMS output loss.\n3. EXT_KILL hardware path must not depend on MCU.\n4. POWER_GND, SIGNAL_GND, ISO_GND and CHASSIS are not automatically shorted."
    (at 20 65 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.8 1.8)) (justify left))
  )
